SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3472
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE MURRAY.
7161H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To repeal sections 328.020 and 328.080, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof three new
sections relating to barber licensure, with penalty provisions.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Sections 328.020 and 328.080, RSMo, are repealed and three new sections
2 enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as sections 328.020, 328.077, and 328.080, to read as
3 follows:
328.020. Except as provided in section 328.077, it shall be unlawful for any person
2 to practice the occupation of a barber in this state, unless he or she shall have first obtained a
3 license, as provided in this chapter.
328.077. 1. The board shall create an establishment training program to allow
2 unlicensed persons to provide barbering services under the supervision of a licensee at a
3 licensed barber establishment. The board shall allow any licensed barber establishment
4 to register to participate in the establishment training program.
5 2. A licensed barber establishment registered under this section may employ a
6 person, without regard to the person's licensure status under this chapter, to provide
7 barbering services that would otherwise require licensure under this chapter. Any
8 person providing such barbering services shall provide the services only under the
9 supervision of a licensee who holds an active license to practice barbering under this
10 chapter and who regularly provides such services in the registered establishment. For
11 purposes of this section, "supervision" means the supervising licensee is physically
12 present with the person providing barbering services and available to assist in providing
13 the services.
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

HB 3472 2
14 3. Before a person provides barbering services without a license under this
15 section, the person shall complete a one-time course of not more than four hours of
16 education regarding sanitation and the laws of this state that is approved or created by
17 the board. Completion of the course may be self-certified by the establishment.
18 4. The board shall not require a person participating in the program to take an
19 examination or the barber establishment to obtain approval of the curriculum for
20 continuing education. The owner of the registered barber establishment shall be
21 responsible for ensuring the education, training, skills, and competence of any person
22 providing services under this section.
23 5. A licensed barber establishment participating in the establishment training
24 program shall comply with all requirements of this chapter and any rules applicable to
25 barber establishments relating to facility standards, sanitation, infection control,
26 inspections, and establishment licensure and renewal.
27 6. Before a consumer receives barbering services from a person providing
28 services without a license under this section, the barber establishment shall provide a
29 written disclosure that is clearly legible and states substantially the following: "This
30 establishment is a licensed barber establishment registered to participate in an
31 establishment training program. This establishment employs unlicensed individuals
32 who provide services under the supervision of licensed barbers. The services you are
33 receiving are from an unlicensed individual participating in this program.".
34 7. A supervising licensee under this section shall not be required to hold a barber
35 instructor license under section 328.090 or a barber apprentice supervisor license under
36 section 328.075 solely in order to supervise a person providing services under this
37 section, and participation in the establishment training program shall not create any
38 new instructor license category.
39 8. The board may suspend or revoke an establishment's registration to
40 participate in the establishment training program for violations of this chapter or
41 corresponding rules, including under circumstances in which the board has probable
42 cause to believe that a person's health or safety has been harmed by an unlicensed
43 person training under this section, and may order the establishment to immediately
44 cease participation pending further proceedings. Any establishment subject to
45 suspension or revocation of registration under this section shall have the right to file
46 a complaint with the administrative hearing commission as provided by chapter 621.
47 9. Participation in the establishment training program under this section shall
48 not subject the participants to the penalties in section 328.160 related to unlicensed
49 practice.

HB 3472 3
50 10. Nothing in this section shall be construed to interfere with barbering
51 apprenticeships.
328.080. 1. Any person desiring to practice barbering in this state shall make
2 application for a license to the board and shall pay the required barber examination fee.
3 2. The board shall examine each qualified applicant and, upon successful completion
4 of the examination and payment of the required license fee, shall issue the applicant a license
5 authorizing him or her to practice the occupation of barber in this state. The board shall admit
6 an applicant to the examination, if it finds that he or she:
7 (1) Is seventeen years of age or older;
8 (2) Is free of contagious or infectious diseases that are capable of being transmitted
9 during the ordinary course of business for a person licensed under this chapter;
10 (3) Either:
11 (a) Has studied for at least one thousand hours in a period of not less than six months
12 in a properly appointed and conducted barber school under the direct supervision of a licensed
13 instructor; or, if the applicant is an apprentice, the applicant shall have served and completed
14 no less than two thousand hours under the direct supervision of a licensed barber apprentice
15 supervisor; or
16 (b) Submits satisfactory proof, signed by the supervising licensee or licensees, of
17 having completed no less than two thousand hours of supervised practice in a registered
18 barber establishment under the establishment training program created in section
19 328.077;
20 (4) Is possessed of requisite skill in the trade of barbering to properly perform the
21 duties thereof, including the preparation of tools, shaving, haircutting and all the duties and
22 services incident thereto; and
23 (5) Has sufficient knowledge of the common diseases of the face and skin to avoid the
24 aggravation and spread thereof in the practice of barbering.
25 3. The board shall be the judge of whether the barber school, the barber
26 apprenticeship, or college is properly appointed and conducted under proper instruction to
27 give sufficient training in the trade.
28 4. The sufficiency of the qualifications of applicants shall be determined by the board.
